{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":560,"text":"We are stealing nature from our children."},{"time":4840,"text":"Now, when I say this, I don't mean\nthat we are destroying nature"},{"time":7920,"text":"that they will have wanted us to preserve,"},{"time":10320,"text":"although that is\nunfortunately also the case."},{"time":13000,"text":"What I mean here is that we've started\nto define nature in a way"},{"time":16840,"text":"that's so purist and so strict"},{"time":19880,"text":"that under the definition\nwe're creating for ourselves,"},{"time":22640,"text":"there won't be any nature\nleft for our children"},{"time":25040,"text":"when they're adults."},{"time":27120,"text":"But there's a fix for this."},{"time":29680,"text":"So let me explain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31680,"text":"Right now, humans use half of the world"},{"time":35160,"text":"to live, to grow their crops\nand their timber,"},{"time":37880,"text":"to pasture their animals."},{"time":39800,"text":"If you added up all the human beings,"},{"time":41640,"text":"we would weigh 10 times as much\nas all the wild mammals put together."},{"time":46800,"text":"We cut roads through the forest."},{"time":49680,"text":"We have added little plastic particles\nto the sand on ocean beaches."},{"time":54040,"text":"We've changed the chemistry of the soil\nwith our artificial fertilizers."},{"time":59160,"text":"And of course, we've changed\nthe chemistry of the air."},{"time":62400,"text":"So when you take your next breath,"},{"time":64280,"text":"you'll be breathing in\n42 percent more carbon dioxide"},{"time":68160,"text":"than if you were breathing in 1750."},{"time":71280,"text":"So all of these changes, and many others,"},{"time":73760,"text":"have come to be kind of lumped together\nunder this rubric of the \"Anthropocene.\""},{"time":78480,"text":"And this is a term\nthat some geologists are suggesting"},{"time":81040,"text":"we should give to our current epoch,"},{"time":82880,"text":"given how pervasive\nhuman influence has been over it."},{"time":86320,"text":"Now, it's still just a proposed epoch,\nbut I think it's a helpful way"},{"time":90200,"text":"to think about the magnitude\nof human influence on the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94800,"text":"So where does this put nature?"},{"time":96520,"text":"What counts as nature in a world\nwhere everything is influenced by humans?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":101400,"text":"So 25 years ago, environmental writer\nBill McKibben said"},{"time":105600,"text":"that because nature\nwas a thing apart from man"},{"time":110120,"text":"and because climate change meant"},{"time":111720,"text":"that every centimeter of the Earth\nwas altered by man,"},{"time":115360,"text":"then nature was over."},{"time":117480,"text":"In fact, he called his book\n\"The End of Nature.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"I disagree with this.\nI just disagree with this."},{"time":124280,"text":"I disagree with this definition of nature,\nbecause, fundamentally, we are animals."},{"time":128639,"text":"Right? Like, we evolved on this planet"},{"time":131480,"text":"in the context of all the other animals\nwith which we share a planet,"},{"time":135600,"text":"and all the other plants,\nand all the other microbes."},{"time":138200,"text":"And so I think that nature"},{"time":140520,"text":"is not that which is untouched\nby humanity, man or woman."},{"time":144600,"text":"I think that nature\nis anywhere where life thrives,"},{"time":148760,"text":"anywhere where there are\nmultiple species together,"},{"time":151800,"text":"anywhere that's green and blue\nand thriving and filled with life"},{"time":155040,"text":"and growing."},{"time":157600,"text":"And under that definition,"},{"time":159520,"text":"things look a little bit different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162080,"text":"Now, I understand that there\nare certain parts of this nature"},{"time":165800,"text":"that speak to us in a special way."},{"time":168440,"text":"Places like Yellowstone,"},{"time":170120,"text":"or the Mongolian steppe,"},{"time":171840,"text":"or the Great Barrier Reef"},{"time":173200,"text":"or the Serengeti."},{"time":174720,"text":"Places that we think of\nas kind of Edenic representations"},{"time":178760,"text":"of a nature before\nwe screwed everything up."},{"time":182560,"text":"And in a way, they are less impacted\nby our day to day activities."},{"time":186600,"text":"Many of these places\nhave no roads or few roads,"},{"time":189320,"text":"so on, like such."},{"time":190920,"text":"But ultimately, even these Edens\nare deeply influenced by humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196720,"text":"Now, let's just take\nNorth America, for example,"},{"time":199000,"text":"since that's where we're meeting."},{"time":200640,"text":"So between about 15,000 years ago\nwhen people first came here,"},{"time":204080,"text":"they started a process\nof interacting with the nature"},{"time":206600,"text":"that led to the extinction\nof a big slew of large-bodied animals,"},{"time":211000,"text":"from the mastodon\nto the giant ground sloth,"},{"time":213280,"text":"saber-toothed cats,"},{"time":214560,"text":"all of these cool animals\nthat unfortunately are no longer with us."},{"time":218200,"text":"And when those animals went extinct,"},{"time":220040,"text":"you know, the ecosystems\ndidn't stand still."},{"time":222640,"text":"Massive ripple effects\nchanged grasslands into forests,"},{"time":226280,"text":"changed the composition of forest\nfrom one tree to another."},{"time":230000,"text":"So even in these Edens,"},{"time":231680,"text":"even in these perfect-looking places"},{"time":233520,"text":"that seem to remind us\nof a past before humans,"},{"time":237040,"text":"we're essentially looking\nat a humanized landscape."},{"time":240960,"text":"Not just these prehistoric humans,\nbut historical humans, indigenous people"},{"time":244560,"text":"all the way up until the moment\nwhen the first colonizers showed up."},{"time":248480,"text":"And the case is the same\nfor the other continents as well."},{"time":251280,"text":"Humans have just been involved in nature"},{"time":254120,"text":"in a very influential way\nfor a very long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258440,"text":"Now, just recently, someone told me,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260240,"text":"\"Oh, but there are still wild places.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":262120,"text":"And I said, \"Where? Where? I want to go.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":264360,"text":"And he said, \"The Amazon.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":266280,"text":"And I was like, \"Oh, the Amazon.\nI was just there."},{"time":269760,"text":"It's awesome. National Geographic\nsent me to Man√∫ National Park,"},{"time":272920,"text":"which is in the Peruvian Amazon,"},{"time":274520,"text":"but it's a big chunk of rainforest,\nuncleared, no roads,"},{"time":278200,"text":"protected as a national park,"},{"time":279840,"text":"one of the most, in fact,\nbiodiverse parks in the world."},{"time":282560,"text":"And when I got in there with my canoe,\nwhat did I find, but people."},{"time":287640,"text":"People have been living there\nfor hundreds and thousands of years."},{"time":291480,"text":"People live there, and they don't\njust float over the jungle."},{"time":294360,"text":"They have a meaningful relationship\nwith the landscape."},{"time":297480,"text":"They hunt. They grow crops."},{"time":299800,"text":"They domesticate crops."},{"time":301320,"text":"They use the natural resources\nto build their houses,"},{"time":304240,"text":"to thatch their houses."},{"time":305520,"text":"They even make pets out of animals\nthat we consider to be wild animals."},{"time":309560,"text":"These people are there"},{"time":311680,"text":"and they're interacting\nwith the environment"},{"time":313800,"text":"in a way that's really meaningful\nand that you can see in the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317320,"text":"Now, I was with\nan anthropologist on this trip,"},{"time":319560,"text":"and he told me, as we were\nfloating down the river,"},{"time":322440,"text":"he said, \"There are\nno demographic voids in the Amazon.\""},{"time":327120,"text":"This statement has really stuck with me,"},{"time":329080,"text":"because what it means\nis that the whole Amazon is like this."},{"time":331960,"text":"There's people everywhere."},{"time":333880,"text":"And many other\ntropical forests are the same,"},{"time":336240,"text":"and not just tropical forests."},{"time":337840,"text":"People have influenced\necosystems in the past,"},{"time":341080,"text":"and they continue\nto influence them in the present,"},{"time":343880,"text":"even in places where\nthey're harder to notice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347720,"text":"So, if all of the definitions of nature\nthat we might want to use"},{"time":352960,"text":"that involve it being\nuntouched by humanity"},{"time":355960,"text":"or not having people in it,"},{"time":357320,"text":"if all of those actually give us\na result where we don't have any nature,"},{"time":362680,"text":"then maybe they're the wrong definitions."},{"time":365120,"text":"Maybe we should define it\nby the presence of multiple species,"},{"time":368640,"text":"by the presence of a thriving life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371440,"text":"Now, if we do it that way,"},{"time":373480,"text":"what do we get?"},{"time":374960,"text":"Well, it's this kind of miracle."},{"time":377360,"text":"All of a sudden,\nthere's nature all around us."},{"time":380160,"text":"All of a sudden,\nwe see this Monarch caterpillar"},{"time":382880,"text":"munching on this plant,"},{"time":384760,"text":"and we realize that there it is,"},{"time":386600,"text":"and it's in this empty lot in Chattanooga."},{"time":390320,"text":"And look at this empty lot."},{"time":391680,"text":"I mean, there's, like, probably,"},{"time":393480,"text":"a dozen, minimum,\nplant species growing there,"},{"time":396440,"text":"supporting all kinds of insect life,"},{"time":398720,"text":"and this is a completely unmanaged space,\na completely wild space."},{"time":403080,"text":"This is a kind of wild nature\nright under our nose,"},{"time":406080,"text":"that we don't even notice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408760,"text":"And there's an interesting\nlittle paradox, too."},{"time":411000,"text":"So this nature,"},{"time":412840,"text":"this kind of wild, untended part"},{"time":415520,"text":"of our urban, peri-urban,\nsuburban agricultural existence"},{"time":419320,"text":"that flies under the radar,"},{"time":421720,"text":"it's arguably more wild\nthan a national park,"},{"time":426160,"text":"because national parks\nare very carefully managed"},{"time":428600,"text":"in the 21st century."},{"time":430360,"text":"Crater Lake in southern Oregon,\nwhich is my closest national park,"},{"time":433960,"text":"is a beautiful example of a landscape\nthat seems to be coming out of the past."},{"time":439160,"text":"But they're managing it carefully."},{"time":440920,"text":"One of the issues they have now\nis white bark pine die-off."},{"time":444520,"text":"White bark pine\nis a beautiful, charismatic --"},{"time":447040,"text":"I'll say it's a charismatic megaflora"},{"time":450080,"text":"that grows up at high altitude --"},{"time":451760,"text":"and it's got all these problems\nright now with disease."},{"time":454760,"text":"There's a blister rust\nthat was introduced,"},{"time":456920,"text":"bark beetle."},{"time":458440,"text":"So to deal with this,\nthe park service has been planting"},{"time":462040,"text":"rust-resistant white bark\npine seedlings in the park,"},{"time":466560,"text":"even in areas that they are\notherwise managing as wilderness."},{"time":470200,"text":"And they're also putting out\nbeetle repellent in key areas"},{"time":473040,"text":"as I saw last time I went hiking there."},{"time":475640,"text":"And this kind of thing is really\nmuch more common than you would think."},{"time":479000,"text":"National parks are heavily managed."},{"time":480720,"text":"The wildlife is kept to a certain\npopulation size and structure."},{"time":483800,"text":"Fires are suppressed."},{"time":485360,"text":"Fires are started."},{"time":486680,"text":"Non-native species are removed."},{"time":488880,"text":"Native species are reintroduced."},{"time":490600,"text":"And in fact, I took a look,"},{"time":491960,"text":"and Banff National Park\nis doing all of the things I just listed:"},{"time":495040,"text":"suppressing fire, having fire,"},{"time":496520,"text":"radio-collaring wolves,\nreintroducing bison."},{"time":498760,"text":"It takes a lot of work to make\nthese places look untouched."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":505080,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":511080,"text":"And in a further irony,\nthese places that we love the most"},{"time":515559,"text":"are the places that we love\na little too hard, sometimes."},{"time":518280,"text":"A lot of us like to go there,"},{"time":519720,"text":"and because we're managing\nthem to be stable"},{"time":522280,"text":"in the face of a changing planet,"},{"time":524360,"text":"they often are becoming\nmore fragile over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527440,"text":"Which means that they're\nthe absolute worst places"},{"time":529920,"text":"to take your children on vacation,"},{"time":531880,"text":"because you can't do anything there."},{"time":533800,"text":"You can't climb the trees."},{"time":535120,"text":"You can't fish the fish."},{"time":536360,"text":"You can't make a campfire\nout in the middle of nowhere."},{"time":539000,"text":"You can't take home the pinecones."},{"time":540680,"text":"There are so many rules and restrictions"},{"time":542609,"text":"that from a child's point of view,"},{"time":544600,"text":"this is, like, the worst nature ever."},{"time":547320,"text":"Because children don't want to hike"},{"time":549960,"text":"through a beautiful landscape\nfor five hours"},{"time":552320,"text":"and then look at a beautiful view."},{"time":554200,"text":"That's maybe what we want to do as adults,"},{"time":556224,"text":"but what kids want to do\nis hunker down in one spot"},{"time":559160,"text":"and just tinker with it,\njust work with it,"},{"time":561400,"text":"just pick it up, build a house,\nbuild a fort, do something like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566160,"text":"Additionally, these sort of Edenic places"},{"time":568720,"text":"are often distant from where people live."},{"time":572000,"text":"And they're expensive to get to.\nThey're hard to visit."},{"time":574960,"text":"So this means that they're\nonly available to the elites,"},{"time":577760,"text":"and that's a real problem."},{"time":581000,"text":"The Nature Conservancy\ndid a survey of young people,"},{"time":584400,"text":"and they asked them, how often\ndo you spend time outdoors?"},{"time":588120,"text":"And only two out of five\nspent time outdoors"},{"time":590680,"text":"at least once a week."},{"time":591920,"text":"The other three out of five\nwere just staying inside."},{"time":594960,"text":"And when they asked them why,\nwhat are the barriers to going outside,"},{"time":599080,"text":"the response of 61 percent was,"},{"time":602080,"text":"\"There are no natural areas near my home.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":606200,"text":"And this is crazy.\nThis is just patently false."},{"time":609920,"text":"I mean, 71 percent of people in the US"},{"time":612920,"text":"live within a 10-minute walk\nof a city park."},{"time":615720,"text":"And I'm sure the figures\nare similar in other countries."},{"time":618400,"text":"And that doesn't even count\nyour back garden,"},{"time":620560,"text":"the urban creek, the empty lot."},{"time":623160,"text":"Everybody lives near nature."},{"time":625080,"text":"Every kid lives near nature."},{"time":627760,"text":"We've just somehow\nforgotten how to see it."},{"time":629840,"text":"We've spent too much time\nwatching David Attenborough documentaries"},{"time":633040,"text":"where the nature is really sexy --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635760,"text":"and we've forgotten how to see the nature\nthat is literally right outside our door,"},{"time":639720,"text":"the nature of the street tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641680,"text":"So here's an example: Philadelphia."},{"time":644480,"text":"There's this cool elevated railway"},{"time":646880,"text":"that you can see from the ground,\nthat's been abandoned."},{"time":649320,"text":"Now, this may sound like the beginning\nof the High Line story in Manhattan,"},{"time":652760,"text":"and it's very similar, except they haven't\ndeveloped this into a park yet,"},{"time":656080,"text":"although they're working on it."},{"time":657640,"text":"So for now, it's still this little\nsort of secret wilderness"},{"time":660840,"text":"in the heart of Philadelphia,"},{"time":662280,"text":"and if you know where the hole is\nin the chain-link fence,"},{"time":665400,"text":"you can scramble up to the top"},{"time":667480,"text":"and you can find this\ncompletely wild meadow"},{"time":670320,"text":"just floating above\nthe city of Philadelphia."},{"time":673200,"text":"Every single one of these plants\ngrew from a seed"},{"time":675560,"text":"that planted itself there."},{"time":676920,"text":"This is completely autonomous,\nself-willed nature."},{"time":679880,"text":"And it's right in the middle of the city."},{"time":682160,"text":"And they've sent people up there\nto do sort of biosurveys,"},{"time":685400,"text":"and there are over 50\nplant species up there."},{"time":688560,"text":"And it's not just plants."},{"time":689840,"text":"This is an ecosystem,\na functioning ecosystem."},{"time":693360,"text":"It's creating soil.\nIt's sequestering carbon."},{"time":695840,"text":"There's pollination going on."},{"time":697760,"text":"I mean, this is really an ecosystem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701400,"text":"So scientists have started calling\necosystems like these \"novel ecosystems,\""},{"time":705280,"text":"because they're often\ndominated by non-native species,"},{"time":707880,"text":"and because they're just super weird."},{"time":709640,"text":"They're just unlike anything\nwe've ever seen before."},{"time":712120,"text":"For so long, we dismissed\nall these novel ecosystems as trash."},{"time":716160,"text":"We're talking about\nregrown agricultural fields,"},{"time":718600,"text":"timber plantations that are not\nbeing managed on a day-to-day basis,"},{"time":722200,"text":"second-growth forests generally,\nthe entire East Coast,"},{"time":724880,"text":"where after agriculture moved west,\nthe forest sprung up."},{"time":729040,"text":"And of course, pretty much all of Hawaii,"},{"time":731680,"text":"where novel ecosystems are the norm,"},{"time":734520,"text":"where exotic species totally dominate."},{"time":737120,"text":"This forest here has Queensland maple,"},{"time":739560,"text":"it has sword ferns from Southeast Asia."},{"time":743160,"text":"You can make your own\nnovel ecosystem, too."},{"time":745240,"text":"It's really simple."},{"time":746480,"text":"You just stop mowing your lawn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":749600,"text":"Ilkka Hanski was an ecologist in Finland,\nand he did this experiment himself."},{"time":753320,"text":"He just stopped mowing his lawn,"},{"time":754920,"text":"and after a few years,\nhe had some grad students come,"},{"time":757480,"text":"and they did sort of\na bio-blitz of his backyard,"},{"time":760000,"text":"and they found 375 plant species,"},{"time":764280,"text":"including two endangered species."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767560,"text":"So when you're up there\non that future High Line of Philadelphia,"},{"time":774040,"text":"surrounded by this wildness,"},{"time":775880,"text":"surrounded by this diversity,\nthis abundance, this vibrance,"},{"time":779680,"text":"you can look over the side"},{"time":780960,"text":"and you can see a local playground\nfor a local school,"},{"time":784240,"text":"and that's what it looks like."},{"time":786200,"text":"These children have, that --"},{"time":788240,"text":"You know, under my definition,"},{"time":789720,"text":"there's a lot of the planet\nthat counts as nature,"},{"time":792120,"text":"but this would be one of the few places\nthat wouldn't count as nature."},{"time":795480,"text":"There's nothing there except humans,\nno other plants, no other animals."},{"time":798880,"text":"And what I really wanted to do"},{"time":800360,"text":"was just, like,\nthrow a ladder over the side"},{"time":802480,"text":"and get all these kids to come up with me\ninto this cool meadow."},{"time":806040,"text":"In a way, I feel like this is\nthe choice that faces us."},{"time":809360,"text":"If we dismiss these new natures\nas not acceptable or trashy or no good,"},{"time":815040,"text":"we might as well just pave them over."},{"time":817640,"text":"And in a world where\neverything is changing,"},{"time":820200,"text":"we need to be very careful\nabout how we define nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823800,"text":"In order not to steal it\nfrom our children,"},{"time":825880,"text":"we have to do two things."},{"time":827840,"text":"First, we cannot define nature\nas that which is untouched."},{"time":832360,"text":"This never made any sense anyway."},{"time":833960,"text":"Nature has not been untouched\nfor thousands of years."},{"time":836480,"text":"And it excludes most of the nature\nthat most people can visit"},{"time":840320,"text":"and have a relationship with,"},{"time":842320,"text":"including only nature\nthat children cannot touch."},{"time":846360,"text":"Which brings me to the second thing\nthat we have to do,"},{"time":849000,"text":"which is that we have to\nlet children touch nature,"},{"time":851520,"text":"because that which\nis untouched is unloved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854040,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":863400,"text":"We face some pretty grim\nenvironmental challenges on this planet."},{"time":867160,"text":"Climate change is among them."},{"time":868720,"text":"There's others too:\nhabitat loss is my favorite thing"},{"time":871240,"text":"to freak out about\nin the middle of the night."},{"time":873960,"text":"But in order to solve them,"},{"time":875320,"text":"we need people --\nsmart, dedicated people --"},{"time":878080,"text":"who care about nature."},{"time":879880,"text":"And the only way we're going to raise up\na generation of people"},{"time":882880,"text":"who care about nature"},{"time":884120,"text":"is by letting them touch nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886320,"text":"I have a Fort Theory of Ecology,"},{"time":888640,"text":"Fort Theory of Conservation."},{"time":890560,"text":"Every ecologist I know,\nevery conservation biologist I know,"},{"time":893800,"text":"every conservation professional I know,"},{"time":895720,"text":"built forts when they were kids."},{"time":898840,"text":"If we have a generation\nthat doesn't know how to build a fort,"},{"time":901800,"text":"we'll have a generation that doesn't\nknow how to care about nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":905000,"text":"And I don't want\nto be the one to tell this kid,"},{"time":907280,"text":"who is on a special program"},{"time":908640,"text":"that takes Philadelphia kids\nfrom poor neighborhoods"},{"time":911120,"text":"and takes them to city parks,"},{"time":912560,"text":"I don't want to be the one to tell him\nthat the flower he's holding"},{"time":915760,"text":"is a non-native invasive weed\nthat he should throw away as trash."},{"time":919760,"text":"I think I would much rather\nlearn from this boy"},{"time":922960,"text":"that no matter\nwhere this plant comes from,"},{"time":925640,"text":"it is beautiful, and it deserves\nto be touched and appreciated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929840,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931080,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}